      "span_text": "During the process of TRAIL-induced apoptosis, activation of the initiator caspase-8 can transmit death signals either through direct activation of the effector caspase-3 or -7, or by means of the proapoptotic Bcl-2 family member Bid, through a mitochondrial pathway.  In this mitochondrial death pathway, the ratio of expression of the proapoptotic Bax protein and the antiapoptotic Bcl-2 or Bcl-X L proteins ultimately determines cell death or survival."
